<node TEXT="Volume 1 - Books of Time" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_967768612" CREATED="1334294428326" MODIFIED="1335486924915" HGAP_QUANTITY="25 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="1 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_167698423" CREATED="1334286909629" MODIFIED="1334296073210"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2in">
      <u><b><font size="2">Volume 1 - BOOKS OF TIME</font></b></u><font size="2"><br/></font><br/><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The vast worlds of the Extal galaxy are governed by the Sacred Books of Time. What transpires on Exodus and other worlds within Extal ultimately reflect onto Earth in dreams and imagination. They are such powerful books that no man has glimpsed a single Sacred Book. They are held and guarded by some of the most powerful Ancients. Only one book is known to be kept by the ancient Dragon Tribes of Exodus.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The first volume tells of the four books as a whole as an overview of what is written plus the written word that governs the galaxies as well. This first book called, "Books Of Time," is never seen by anyone. It is beyond reach.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The Balance Crystals of Exodus house part of the energy that flows out of the ancient books. From the Crystals, all life is balanced on Exodus as it is the most sacred world in the Ancient Realm. Without the Crystals' energy, all life on Exodus as well as anywhere on any number of inhabited worlds within the galaxy, would cease to exist. All that has been known would vanish and cut the life blood of pure imagination from the firstborn.<br/><br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The First "Book of Time" governs time within Extal. In certain parts of the Universe, time is slowed down or speeds up according to the laws governed by Father Time who lives in between worlds. In the Books, he writes what is told by God, the order of things to happen and when. The hand of God is written on all four Books of Time and they obey His commands. Such books are forbidden to man.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Volume 2 - The Curse" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1867614173" CREATED="1334294403077" MODIFIED="1335486927743">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_667016087" CREATED="1334286915210" MODIFIED="1334296111842"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2in">
      <u><b><font size="2">Volume 2 - THE CURSE</font></b></u><font size="2"><br/></font><br/><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">5,000 years ago on Exodus, the firstborn race invaded the world with their impure imagination and designs. With the firstborn's introduction of evil, death was whispered on the winds of all time, crippling and unbalancing the Ancient Home World and worlds within all of Extal.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The Ancients, knowing the protection of their own King Elyon was on this race, pleaded with man to make peace and stop the destruction their very presence induced. It went unheeded and turned many Ancients to darkness, avoiding all man.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The race of Dragonborn is part human and part other from the forgotten age when humans bargained with the gods of Extal and cursed themselves for all time.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">Redeemed with truth and Elyon's own grace, they became the protectors of both ancients, native creatures and humans. It was told that with the Dragonborn's coming, a temporary balance would restore Exodus till a time that the books of time would be opened and written on by Elyon Himself.<br/><br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The Second Book of Time, "The Curse," writes the account of man's evil. From the book, the curse is written and poured out upon Extal for man's evilness. Detailed in the ways of which the curse is brought, the book contains death and is forbidden to all. It has been written in a curse but is promised to be written in again to break the curse.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Volume 3 - Gate Bridges" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_381537086" CREATED="1334294357289" MODIFIED="1335486931364">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1276064744" CREATED="1334286918816" MODIFIED="1334296136971"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2in">
      <u><b><font size="2">Volume 3 - GATE BRIDGES</font></b></u><font size="2"><br/></font><br/><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">On Extal worlds, certain parts of the galaxy is linked via gatebridges, portals that connect two points within the system, created before Dragonborn or humans came to inhabit the galaxy. It's true orign is unknown but have been marked by Dragonborn's passing, including the Hight Latra symbols of their language among the most ancient of writings that even they do not fully understand.<br/><br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The Third Book, "Gate Bridges," contains the secrets of traveling via the gatebridge. It is a book of power like all four books of time, therefore giving power to rewrite and reinvent certain things. It is housed in a Great Temple in Dragonborn's Realm, under the protection of an Ancient who is not part of Exodus nor Earth and whose allegience is only to Elyon. It is a book that is to be given to the next Drugi-ward, the guardian of the Gates. At the end of the Third Age, the last Drugi-ward disappeared giving control of the gatebridge over to anyone, the book itself no longer controlling events and countering the darkness that comes from the deep dark.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Volume 4 - Prophecy of Dragons" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1239469874" CREATED="1334294175740" MODIFIED="1335486933995" HGAP_QUANTITY="21 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-11 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1487423132" CREATED="1334286921743" MODIFIED="1334296162507"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2in">
      <u><b><font size="2">Volume 4 - PROPHECY OF THE DRAGONS</font></b></u><font size="2"><br/></font><br/><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The Fourth and final book is called, "Prophecy of Dragons." It is a long and almost forgotten tale. It is a story of what is to come through the ages. Nothing can change it's progress as it was decreed by Elyon Himself to the inhabitants of Exodus. It's tale marks Dragonborn's role as ambassadors for the humans, Elyon's chosen people. It tells of events that will predate certain dark times as well as ages of growth. Ultimately however, it tells of Exodus' own fall and the destruction of all Extal.<br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">Nothing can hold this event back. It is said that Elyon spoke to the First King of Dragonborn, Eskaver Garland, in a dream and gave visions of what was to come. Writing these things down, Eskaver vowed before God to restore his own people back to Elyon's grace. It is told that in the end, a pilgrimage will be made by all humans out of Extal back to their homeworld before the darkness takes over. Still, going home will not prove good because with the fall of Exodus, Earth will finally be what the gods all want, theirs for the taking. In the human Bible, it would be recorded in Revelations.<br/><br/></font><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font><font size="2">The prophecy itself is divided in many sections, given to many different ages, to be held by the priests of Antioch and the Ancient Temple Priests. Each age is given a revelation and a condition by Elyon to return to Him. Even so far away from home, His eyes are always watchful of his chosen people.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
