<node TEXT="1. Concerning The &quot;Balance Crystals&quot;" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1501936270" CREATED="1334294560213" MODIFIED="1335486944365" HGAP_QUANTITY="141 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="497 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1804379216" CREATED="1334287172720" MODIFIED="1334289838883" HGAP_QUANTITY="71 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-1 px"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.2in">
      <u><b><font size="2" color="#33cc00">1. Concerning The "Balance Crystals"</font></b></u><font size="2"><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; &#xa0; </b>It is recorded that at the end of the forgotten age, crystals were formed with the help of Ancients to stop the destruction of Exodus brought on by man's overwhelming power and hunger for knowledge. With this knowledge, man became too powerful for themselves to control their own desires and brought chaos onto the world. Destruction and death reigned down till Exodus shook to it's core threatening to implode. It is not known how but with the help of the Ancients, crystals were formed around the world. Within these crystals housed the magical ability to control the world's destructive nature.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Within each crystal on a continent (which can be one or more), there are swords that were placed within the crystals themselves. If ever the case was that a crystal were to shatter, the swords would be removed and prophecy would be invoked to an Ancient. The Ancient then would bring the swords to the bearer with whom Elyon (God Himself) indicated.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>During the time of Stephen Sherwin, son of Cynric Sherwin, the White Council was growing in it's greed for power once more. From beyond the plains of the living, a general by name of Vincent wanted nothing more than the destruction of the living, the only goal of his master.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Thinking he had found one of the twin Crystals of Balance, he destroyed the crystal itself and took the swords.<br/>In turn, Dragonborn made war on their own home which Vincent had made residence in to retrieve the swords. If the swords were to ever reach Neverworld, the world of the dead, the already tainted swords would gain the Emperor a portion of the power he has always wanted but was never able to obtain through the dark magic.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>The crystal swords are a part of the crystals themselves and hold the world of Exodus together. When the crystal shatters, the power of that crystal transfers to the swords. The magic is the sword and the one who weilds the sword controls the magic of the sword and part of the destructive nature of the world.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Thus, is the reason prophecy is given to the Ancients to distribute the swords specificlly to certain people God chooses to hide the swords or to use them within reason.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
<node ID="ID_524602005" CREATED="1334288382145" MODIFIED="1334288750726"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2" color="#00cc00">1a. CRYSTAL OF ADRYLIN:</font></b><font size="2"><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>There are two locations on Exodus that houses two massive crystals that govern all other crystals of Exodus. They are the Balance Crystals. If ever they are tainted or destroyed, the world will be changed forever. For milleniums, these twin crystals were hidden from everyone's knowledge, kept safe by guardians and magic.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>In the 4th age, when Dragonborn was beginning it's decline, they abandoned one of their first calls.<br/>Ardil, a boy who had visions and was spoken to by angels and Ancients, became an unlikely hero not born of the dragon but chosen by Elyon to lead a war for one of the Balance Crystals.<br/></font><br/><b><font size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">On the half dead continent of Scaron, the Emperor of Night's empire stood in the living ages ago.<br/>On the still thriving living half of the continent but still haunted, the crystal is found and an army is being formed secretly by the darkness. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">It was told that the Twin Balance Crystals were given over to both humans and Ancients to watch. Of Adrylin, the fault seems to lie with the elves, particularlly the Elliads when they discovered their dark brothers were indeed the Nithi. They may have abandoned Scaron completely and Adrylin altogether keeping only a few scouts to report back home from time to time. As to dragons who still recide on parts of Scaron, who knows their minds?<br/></font><br/><b><font size="2">&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">On Legend Island, home of the gods and servants of the Emperor, Ardil must flee when he chooses to side with the forbidden God and sets out on a quest to warn Dragonborn of the events taking place while they themselves are quietly wasting away in a madness that is threatening to take over their minds.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; &#xa0; </b>Through danger, forbidden love, and a wild quest leading to all parts of the world he never knew he would ever see, Ardil is a prominent player in the role of keeping the Crystal of Adrylin safe from destruction.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>In the end, the Crystal of Adrylin is saved and once again protected and guarded fiercely by dragons who make it a permanent second home.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0; </b>As for Ardil, he disappears from the pages of history who get too close to the truth.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_710729579" CREATED="1334288390143" MODIFIED="1334288771954"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2" color="#00cc00">1b. CRYSTAL OF TAUSA:</font><font size="2"><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">At the very center of the Volesin Sea sits the Island of Tausa. It is not visible to the naked eye and cannot be accidently sailed into. It cannot be touched except by one who is granted permission by the Drugi-ward (gatekeeper). As the Drugi-ward controls the Gatebridge of which Dragonborn travels, he also holds the secrets of Exodus.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>In the age that Dragonborn betrayed the royal House of Sherwin and exiled the family, they set in motion things that would play out to their own demise and catastrophic events.<br/></font><br/><b><font size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">It is with these events that darkness gained a foothold and the Drugi-ward himself was captured. With the faith in Elyon gone in Dragonborn, the hand of Elyon over Exodus was slowly retracting. The power once held, now was no longer there. The Drugi-ward, held in secret by Elyon Himself, could not be contained any longer. Neverworld found him and the secrets he guarded. The gatebridge was taken over and made unsafe for leasure travel. And with the capture of the Drugi-ward, the Island of Tausa was no longer under the Drugi-ward's protection.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>With the capture of the Drugi-ward, Neverworld went for the Crystal of Tausa and shattered it whole. With Dragonborn's own betrayal of the royal house, they sided with the White Council making themselves little more than puppets. The Island of Tausa was unguarded.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>The results were worldwide earthquakes and wild storms that surged uncontrollably throughout the heavens that were not seen since before the Forgotten Age.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>When it was discovered what had happened, it was already too late. The damage was done.<br/>The swords that were contained within the Crystal of Tausa were taken by the Neverworld soldiers. And this time, the swords taken were from a Balance Crystal that could destroy worlds.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="2. Concerning Vale Sherwin and Valandil Faelivrin" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1312375471" CREATED="1334294579952" MODIFIED="1335486945739" HGAP_QUANTITY="138 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="4 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_67929286" CREATED="1334287179490" MODIFIED="1334289827523" HGAP_QUANTITY="72 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-11 px"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font size="2" color="#33cc00">2. Concerning Vale Sherwin &amp; Ravage</font></b></u><b><font size="2"><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">There's an incident that occured at the same time the Crystal of Tausa was destroyed. This incident pertains to the bloodline of Sherwin and the bloodline of the Emperor of Night.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Ravage has always been known for his terror throughout the ages. His age is unknown but is ancient in human years.<br/>When Vale Sherwin of the exiled family regained the lost Sword of Dragon's Fire, he had earned the right to lead the creatures of Exodus and the Dragons themselves against Neverworld's war raging across Exodus.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Upon reaching the Island of Tausa, Vale found to his dismay the crystal shattered and the swords gone. It is also here that he meets Ravage once again for he has met the prince several times before in the past while doing his father's business. However, while doing so, Vale senses that something disturbs this otherwise undead prince.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Ravage proceeds to tell Vale his own story, breaking his long held silence through the ages, revealing his true origins as Prince Valandil Faelivrin, the prince of the Emperor of Night. When this shocking news has finished settling into Vale and his companions who are with him, Ravage tells his own story of how he has been visited by otherworldly creatures, not by Ancients but by beings far more powerful than any he has ever met before. They tell him that his days are numbered if his ways are not changed. There is still hope for him but he must seek out one named Vale Sherwin who will tell him more of what to do.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>When Teldan, Vale's close friend, asks why Ravage chose to follow this creature's advice, Ravage replies that he simply knows in his heart that he must follow. Even if it is to defy the Emperor, he must ask Vale what it is he must do. He knows it was an Amtuvo (angel).<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>With Vale's help along with Teldan's, they begin to turn Ravage from the darkness he has served or more to the point acted as in Neverworld. At the same time, he gives over secrets of the Emperor that nobody has known of before.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Even so, it may be too late. Dragonborn is falling as it has been prophecied before. It has given itself to the White Council. The Royal House of Sherwin is exiled. The Dragons and Ancients are enraged at everyone but the Sherwins.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>It seemed that within weeks, war seemed to quickly die out and the White Council won victoriously against Neverworld. That itself made no sense which Ravage explained. The White Council was intended to win without knowing. Magic was to be introduced into Exodus again on a wide scale. His father was setting the stage for something much bigger to come.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>While they were walking down a hillside one day examing the bodies of the fallen, the clouds split revealing red thunder and charriots. Black winged monsters of no description whipped down to eradicate all in it's path including Ravage but most of all, Vale.<br/>It was decided from there that Vale was not safe at all. He knew too much and Ravage had put him in danger of the Emperor himself. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">But at the same time, the White Council had gained too much power and as was told by reports, Dragonborn itself was being looked upon as the enemy.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; &#xa0;</b>With their faith gone and the Ancients unsupport, they were helpless. Soon, Dragonborn would have to flee for their lives as would Vale and his own friends.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>To Ravage, Vale gave the sword of Dragon's Fire to keep safe. It needed to be guarded and if need be, to guide the Ancients. War would come. And they needed to follow the sword. The sword was given to Ravage freely by Vale Sherwin. It would be known magically by the sword itself.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; &#xa0;</b>As for the Sherwin Family, they would go into hiding until the time was right to take the throne again</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="History of Gontha" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1451121632" CREATED="1334290054100" MODIFIED="1335486948478" HGAP_QUANTITY="140 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-683 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1663201296" CREATED="1334290191766" MODIFIED="1334290573028"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2">~~ </font><font size="2" color="#33cc00">Before Humans</font></b><font size="2"><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;In the beginning, God created the Heavens and the Earth....<br/>The Second of Three Heavens is vast beyond understanding. It is a strange and untamed place where man was never meant to exist naturally. There is a place that borders all three Heavens within the Universe. It is from which dreams are formed and mythology of man lives. It is called Exodus by man but in it's own language, Ellavian.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;There was once 2 main continents on the western half of the world. One was called Gontha, the other was called Sacris. It was a world of beauty and untamed wild magic where all creatures were born from man's imagination and under the ancient laws that govern the Universe. Upon the lands, creatures great and small lived the dreams of man and formed the imaginations fueling creation's ambitions where upon man became great or small depending on one's own imagination and extent of it.<br/><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Upon Gontha was formed the first half of the whole which governed the world and dreams with order, man's own dreams creating temples and monuments, structures great and small throughout all the lands as a testament to God's greatness in creation and man's form and deeds structured after God's own image. For man is God's greatest creation. He is God's own children where upon all creation bows in the awesomness of God.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;From the Silas creatues of fairy lands and nymphs who play games forever to the plainlands of Percva'm's unicorn herds and fields of splendor and power of it's radiant temples to Calmone's waterfalls and magic of sea and land to mimic man's own ideas of beauty, all was set in order.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;And into the lands of myth was formed the races of Ancients: Elves of the secondborn, formed partly in the image of man but whole only in the magic lands and forest meadows, Dwarves: smaller than elves and stubborn to a fault, craving all things metallic and rock who's mountains are the glory of God. Into the reaches, they delve to create masterworks to sparkle in the golden sun to behold the power of Ellavian's crystals, Phantoms: the winged messengers of earth and sky who travel the clouds with thoughts of order and splendor, Giants: beasts akin to elves but taller and walks the northern territories with trembling stones announcing their presence, Dragons: the master race of all mythology who's very presence is God's reminder of authority over all creation.<br/>&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;There are many more creatures such as centaurs, dryads, trolls and all that man has dreamed since the beginning of creation. Ellavian is filled with history of mythology and testaments to God's wonder and imagination worked out by man's own dreams.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_241015159" CREATED="1334290194906" MODIFIED="1334291797174"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2">~~ </font><font color="#33cc00" size="2">After Humans</font></b><font size="2"><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;At the beginning since Adam and Eve broke the universal wholeness with one greed of sin, all of creation tore apart; for man was meant to be the heirs of God, children of creation but above angels, rulers under God's own High Command. When sin entered the perfection of Earth, all creation groaned with the taint of evil, the lack of God. For where evil exists, God cannot be in it's presence nor it in His. For Light destroys all that is dark. And Adam damned the heirs of God to lives of darkness.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;With provision made for humans alone for what was done, no other creation is granted mistakes. Humans alone are blessed as children unto God and forever are protected when the eyes are opened.<br/><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;But man through the centuries are historically wicked at heart, touched by darkness and it wanting humanity to die in ignorance of grace. So when man achieved what he thought impossible, with man was carried the taint of evil even to the world between worlds, the dreamworld of Exodus as man has such named it for themselves.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;In the beginning, man was curious and filled with awe at the new and unexplainable things seen. Here was a world where they could live and breath without aid. Here also was energy in a form he could not understand.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;So began man's existence on Exodus, creating a city and colonizing the world, exploration teams spreading in all directions.<br/>Still...it was not enough for one man, the leader of the expedition.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;James Faelivrin was a greedy man given to temperments and outbursts, never pleased and wanting more.<br/>When he saw that Gontha housed many energies he could not understand, he spent all of his time studying the creatures of which were part of this energy, enslaving and torturing to understand what made them exist.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;History is uncertain what exactly turned James Faelivrin but he did turn and in a dark way upon which the main scientific community questioned his ethics and morals. Given to drink and darker deeds, he was soon banned from the city of lights, the largest city that expanded over the years since man first came to Gontha.<br/><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;From the pages of history it is recorded that Dragonborn was formed from the dark experiments James Faelivrin continued though it is never clear as to how other than that it forever altered the men and women and their children's children for all time.<br/>In the later years of the Forgotten Age, Dragonborn escaped the prison they were part of within the mind and out, controlled by Faelivrin's first of many creations of abomination.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Fleeing Faelivrin's built up city, they wandered as nomads in the wilderness and seeing for the first time the effect man's own presence placed on Exodus' natives. Death was the reward for man's coming, the taint of sin touching all life, killing many native beings of magic and beauty.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;For many years, the first Dragonborn fled from the wrath of Faelivrin and divided into several tribes, always connected via the mainframe. In this way, they kept watch over each other at great distance and informing of Faelivrin's rage and determination to take them back. Dragonborn after all was Faelivrin's greatest achievment...and threat.<br/><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;After the third Council of Elders, Dragons and a few others of the most powerful Ancients came together to form a treaty with Dragonborn. It was clear that they were not like most men who now populated much of Gontha. Also, a Phantom was given a message to deliver to the Elder Council by the hand of Elyon Himself.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Soon after, Dragonborn as a whole sided with the Ancients forming the first treaty of man and Ancients. More specifically, Ancients and Dragonborn as emmisaries between both sides. Under cover of magic man never could attain, which infuriated Faelivrin, Dragonborn was lost to Faelivrin's ever determination to find his lost experimental subjects.<br/><br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;In this time, with the help of many Ancient races, the first Dragon Palace for human inhabitation was created. Large by any normal man's standard, it was built this way for the purpose of housing all Ancient races including giants and Dragons. Each province of the Dragonsrealm is divided into territories large enough for many tribes of the same nation without crowding.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;It fell to Dragonborn to create a system of government headed by Dragons and Dragonborn. To each province then was placed a guardian, ancient or human to be Lord of the lands and a speaker for his or her subjects in the Great Dragon Hall where all things were discussed.<br/>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The country was also designed to withstand attacks from outside. Fortified with a wall, the entire country was built within the Great Wall upon the Dragon Mountains in the Midland Region. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in" align="center">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in" align="center">
      <b><strike><font size="2">. -=o&#xa7;o=- .</font></strike></b>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2"><br/>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">For 500 years, things seemed to work out well. Dragonborn kept to an ordered system and became known throughout Gontha as Peace Keepers. Families were born and continued the legacy began with their forefathers, each living a great long life, greater than many normal humans.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>At the end of 500 years though, an uprising came from all corners of the continent. Greed tainted many man's heart for the source of power within the Ancients. Man beheld the wonders of magic and wanted it for themselves to control. Thus began the first of many dark wars that have forever been lost to man. It is now chronicled in the Ancient Dragonborn Journals in the Hall of Records.<br/>Within this record, it tells of man's dark choices and the beginning of man's turn to other means to control elements of Exodus.<br/>Gods, they believed, spoke to them in dreams, promising great power that equaled or even mastered over the Ancient races.<br/>At the head of this, Faelivrin came out and claimed himself the Emperor of Exodus, the High Priest of nine gods who told him secrets of the Ancient order. Few believed his claim but his reputation was known throughout the entire vast continent.<br/>To get the attentio of the scientists who had followed after their own forefathers, Faelivrin made an example of them by casting lightning down upon them all burning them alive on the University steps for all to see via comports. Here ended the greatest scientists upon Exodus.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>From here, Faelivrin raised army after army and began a march throughout all of Gontha to imprison or irradicate Ancients claiming they were tainted with evil.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>From within Dragonsrealm, the Council was heated in debate. Under universal law, Ancients were forbidden to harm humans as they were made in the image of the Creator and His children.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>It fell upon Dragonborn to decide their involvement in Faelivrin's extermination process. Faelivrin had gained much power over 500 years and also something else that spelled death to many Ancients. To walk near Faelivrin was instant death for what was now part of him. A black magic was being called from the real powers that now converged on Exodus making it their second home.<br/>It became clear then what was needed.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>With the help of the master dwarf smiths, the magic of the elder elves and the deepest magic of Dragons, a single sword was created of flame and blood. Magic in all ways, it held vast power. Now all that was needed was to choose who to wield the weapon.<br/>For many weeks it was undecided and with these weeks, Dragonborn went to war against Faelivrin head on. In the chronicles, it is titled "The Holy War." For it truly was more than a mortal fight. It was the war of gods.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>He is simply called Eskaver. Nothing much is known except he led many people who were caught in the middle of the war. Thinking more for their safety, Eskaver led many ventures into small towns, guns blazing all around. Faelivrin had little care for his own people. He would cut them down if they were in his way to capture an Ancient being.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>It fueled Eskaver with rage and he was quickly known as the Bizzerker. Of all men, he seemed to be untouchable and was. For within his heart, he prayed feverently to be kept safe only so that he could save those from Faelivrin's slaughter.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>One day when he was rescuing a city from the inevitable tide of abomidable creatures created by Faelivrin, two other Dragonborn approached him in the fields, two senior dragons carrying them on their backs which was seldom seen.<br/>It was decided. Eskaver was given the Dragon Sword.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>It should have turned the tide with the power of magic at Eskaver's finger tips. But what it did was infuriate Faelivrin. Here he was fighting to attain the magic for himself and traitors who he created to be more than they ever had been was given this magic.<br/>In a blind madness, Faelivrin stepped up the war, massacering all in his way. Rivers flowed with blood and the body count of innocents were higher than any human could stand. Those that had willingly sided with him deserted and went into hiding as all things living did except those who opposed his dark army.<br/></font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <b><font size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </font></b><font size="2">History forgets the event but evidence is on maps. With his furious rage, Faelivrin abandoned reason and listened to darker words, succuming to a decision he wouldn't have made till then. Drawing all the forces together into one field, enemy and his own alike, from the heavens, he had built a ship of exploration. More than exploration though was the weapons that were designed before all the scientists were killed off. It was a bomb that made the Atomic Bomb look simple in comparison.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>When each force of the war was gathered, he let the dark dreams of madness take hold. With a single press of the button, Exodus forever changed.<br/><br/><b>&#xa0; &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Light and darkness collided and bled as fire and the dark creation of man exploded. Nobody was safe as the weapon hit ground. It spread like a volcanic plate beneath the ground, shifting back and forth till all things were swallowed whole by a gaping hole spewing fire. It did not end however but kept on spreading like a disease upon the very land, eroding earth and all that was in it's path. Water from the north and south crashed inward with billowing steam as Gontha was being torn apart faster than could be imagined. From north to south, the split in the ground was almost instantanious. East and west, the ground fell apart bit by bit with earthquakes tearing the land apart till after three full days, all that remained was a giant mass of water where once Gontha stood whole. The armies of both sides had vanished within the waters.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>From that day forward, Ancients turned inward making little to no contact with any human. For man, he renamed Gontha "Elise" for the western half and "Eden" for the eastern half. Between the two halves, they named the waterway the "Volesin Sea." It was a time of great mourning for loss of more than lives.<br/><b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </b>Technology that once existed was forever lost by the destructive nature Faelivrin used in his weapon. For it wiped out all power on both sides of the once Gontha. It was a time of reinventing man's life from that of a great and powerful people to helpless people lost to their precious electrical power that was the lifeblood of civilization.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="1st Chaos War" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1763831586" CREATED="1334295052353" MODIFIED="1335486953285" HGAP_QUANTITY="75 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="-964 px">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1889569777" CREATED="1334295123332" MODIFIED="1334295192602"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">1st Chaos War:</font></b></u>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">The first Chas War was fought in the forgotten age when technology still existed. After the scientists took control of what they could claim of Exodus's largest continent, Gontha, they made themselves gods. The colonies revolted fiercely bringing about the destruction of all technology and bringing in the first age of Exodus. In this age, the people simply returned to the Medival times of Earth. They set up rulers to govern over local affairs.When this happened, the natives of the land simply drew apart from the colonies but was not yet cut off.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="1st Age: Age of the 2nd Chaos War / Second Holy War" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1534002233" CREATED="1334295273848" MODIFIED="1335486956548">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1061084539" CREATED="1334295289842" MODIFIED="1334295403375"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">1st Age: Age of the 2nd Chaos War / Second Holy War </font></b></u>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The 1st age brought about the White Council, the aftermath of the Forgotten age where Dragonborn fought fiercely against Base, the colonized dark and magical realm of the High Council. As the 1st age dawned, the High Council of Base was silenced for a time. It was thought the great wars of Chaos was over. But in the middle of the millenium, 1500 years after, the White Council grew in power becoming popular once again. Thus the beginning of the Holy Wars was started.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; It didn't grow popular till the middle of the millenium. Through it, Christianity practically died away. In it's place magic swarmed the everyday lifestyle and the White Council was the temple dedicated to almost every god the priests could come up with. They did this only to bring power to themselves and rule over Elise. They had little knowledge of the power they could command till later.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; As the decades passed, the White Council grew as it's priests became gods in their own right. From all across Gontha, natives swarmed into a madness never seen before or since in the land. They besieged the White Council along with a certain human known only as Eskaver Garland. He was the first Dragonborn to appear in the history of Exodus in written form. In his hand was a sword of unnatural fire; it's power beyond understanding. With it he marched on the White Council with the aid of the unnatural allies, those who feared humans, the natives.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Blood ran freely throughout Gontha as the Holy Wars brought forth revolts from all across the continent of Gontha. The people were split in half. For and against the White Council. Those who supported the White Council were those who saw the power of magic and how it could affect them for the good of all. They had in mind a better place, a place governed totally by magic and the White Council's seemingly innocent ways. Those who had been on Exodus before humans arrived knew the difference though and were terrified of this unnatural magic humans wielded. It was the most bloody war and also the war that split Gontha in two parts in the frenzy of a war gone mad.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Gontha was forever changed into the continents of Elise and Eden with the Volesin Ocean dividing the two. The name 'Gontha' is not even known today to anyone due mainly to the fact that most of the early writings of Exodus history is written primarily in the ancient Latra script. None but a very few know this language because it's a dead language. Those who speak it are the ancients and the few giants, elves and others who survived the coming of humans that marked the end of their own lives through the taint of man's heart.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="2nd Age: Age of the &quot;Knight of the Sword&quot;" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1002775258" CREATED="1334295429979" MODIFIED="1335486958228">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_216340866" CREATED="1334295481658" MODIFIED="1334295555997"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">2nd Age: Age of the "Knight of the Sword" </font></b></u>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The 2nd age is the age of Dragonborn in most historian collections. The term "Knight of the Sword" is not understood to most people except Dragonborn who guarded it's meaning. It's the age of Cynric Sherwin, a foreign stranger to Rumeran.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; His tale is lost in most accounts being it's blasphamy against the 9 gods. In it, records show he was from another world, a world refered to as the Home World where all mankind came from. This is the total opposite of what the 9 gods of Exodus say. They say that each of the 9 gods created certain men and women along with the creatures of Exodus called natives. Though it is considered cruel, the 9 gods make war agaisnt each other, wanting to be the higher god. So they include man in their game of chess moving the inhabitants of their created world according to their will. Those who pray to certain gods, the gods bless. The gods who don't get the prayers are angered and make life miserable. So in most cases, the calendar of Exodus was devised for the civilized countries that are under the White Council. Thus they are able to pray to all 9 gods to appease their wrath.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Cynric's tale is told of how he was tricked into stepping into a portal ending in the land of Rumeran. There he was forced to rescue the Princess whose god had declared her to be a sacrifice for her people because she had turned against him. Throughout the tale, Cynric is given the name "Knight of the Sword" though he knows nothing of Dragonborn's history.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; When understanding comes at last after some years, he built the 1st sanctuary of Christains who were the minority and the hunted by magical beasts and dark plots in all the civilized countries. Thus Antioch was formed on the east coast of Elise, obscured and barred by a desert land full of death. The desert is called the Wilderlands, south of the Verlone forest and north of the country of Dunland. It is a testament to the 1st age of the Holy Wars; the lands there scarred beyond recovery. No man or animal lives there if not necessary.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; The White Council was powerful though. So powerful terror ran through man's hearts, even those who worshipped the gods of the White Council. It wasn't long before Anitoch was found and the inhabitants fled.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; In another story, Dragonborn is said to be on the Home world where several of the refugee's fled to by the power Cynric posessed. Vincent, the Darklord of old, high priest of the White Council demanded revenge against Dragonborn. What is truly stunning is Vincent is the father of Cynric Sherwin. This evidence almost destroyed Dragonborn when they were rescuing the ancient Swords of Dragons Fire. They stood firm in the end though and guards remained at the entrance of the Crystal temples, the most ancient but forgotten buildings.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="3rd Age: Age of the 3rd War of Chaos" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_834943664" CREATED="1334295572867" MODIFIED="1335486960186">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_278675102" CREATED="1334295597948" MODIFIED="1334295711959"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">3rd Age: Age of the 3rd War of Chaos </font></b></u>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The 3rd age is a dark age in Exodus' history. Dragonborn is known as the protectors of Exodus as are their brothers, the Guardians that recided in Scaron. But in the year of "3100" of the 3rd age, the realm of Dragonborn split in two causing a Civil War between brothers.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; The ancient realm of the Highlands of the Midlands crumbled on itself as the Forbidden God was forgotten. Several fractions sided finally with the White Council, seeing the Council's power as did those in the early days of the Holy Wars. Thus Dragonborn feuded with each other. Angry that brothers would side with the ancient enemy of so many thousands of years, the war took on a new form, one that stripped apart Dragonborn's realm with power of technology. On the Home World even, battles took place in space far from the eyes and ears of the majority who knew nothing of Dragonborn's existance. In the end, Dragonborn fell on itself, the war ending the protection of Exodus.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Several centuries later, around "3500", Dragonborn reformed itself on the home world bringing back those who had turned away. Some brang with them pasts shrouded in darkness and misery that scarred their hearts and souls. It was an age of mourning, of silent understanding. Several doned black clothing for most of their lives identifying with the horror of what happened when embracing the darkness.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; In the lead of heading up the reformation of Dragonborn was Stephen Sherwin, the son of Cynric Sherwin of the 2nd age, bringing together all who were Dragonborn around Earth as well as Exodus's scattered inhabitants of Dragonborn. He drew them together with his own compassion and own trials being faced with the past and the ever watching of his father's decline since the discovery of his own heritage of the ancient enemy. He had long since disappeared and Stephen dealt with it all.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; One day though, after rescuing a police officer who had gained unusual information concerning Dragonborn's Castle on Exodus, Cynric appeared to him and those with him briefly. They had learned of the Darklord's residence in Castle Dragonborn along with the horror of his attempt to take the one of the Crystals of Balance that sustained life on Exodus. With his touch, the Crystal forever was tainted. He had also retrieved the swords found in the Crystal for his own use. Dragonborn thus made war upon their own realm again to rescue the swords and to take back their land.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Through the years since, Exodus knew no peace. Because of the disappearance of Dragonborn for a time, darkness swarmed over the lands with it's magic and influence. Races of men changed in ways unheard of, terrifying to some extents. On the continent of Eden just for example, Soalmin, once bordermen protecting the coasts and mountains of the west changed drastically into the most feared of all warriors, devising and perfecting tortures and the total enslavery of man. The Usilian Wars speak of this when King Usilian came to the throne of of Cavor.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; The 3rd age closed with Dragonborn still not as strong as in the earlier days but still retained outposts and the rebuilt Kingdom of Dragonborn in the Midlands.</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="4th Age: Age of the Crystal War" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1202206612" CREATED="1334295739064" MODIFIED="1335486961948">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_343991932" CREATED="1334295770599" MODIFIED="1334295831833"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <u><b><font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">4th Age: Age of the Crystal War </font></b></u>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The 4th age was given to blindness and the ever increasing darkness as Dragonborn tried desperately to hold onto their outposts in lands that were outside of Midland. A tale is kept in the vaults of Dragonborn.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Ardil, a lone wanderer, had been given a task of utmost importance. He must deliver a message to the Dragonborns. From Legend Island, his home, to the Tarkon valley near Silver lake on Eden, he travels and makes friends who will stand beside him in the darkening days. One such is an elf princess, one who's love for him is unmatched though the elven nation of Ardol would be furious at such a notion. But circumstances make her flee her own homeland for fear of death, not because of her love for Ardil, but because she has turned her back on Tarris, the star god and the god of the elves. For joining with the Forbidden God, she has sentenced herself to death even as a princess.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; The 4th age increased in darkness with the rise of Vincent once again, thought to have died when Dragonborn was taking back their realm. Yet he was alive, his new realm born out of Tausin who's history should have made people suspicious.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; As legend goes, Tausin use to be the realm of prosperity and power. All throughout Scaron, Tausin was known as the empire of dreams. It was here that wisdom and knowledge was taught. The legend splits into many different stories and forms that concludes with the empire of Tausin changed somehow into a mysterious place shrouded in darkness. After a time, the legend of Tausin ceased to say more. Ages passed since any human stepped foot beyond the Gates.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; There was only one way into the realm of Tausin. It was through the Gates of Darkness. Rumors of the gate's name are as many as the legends of Tausin itself. The most favored one though is that the greed and power of such knowledge from Tausin's extensive libraries and schools proved deadly. From beyond the grave, death swarmed through the entire empire striking out with plagues and an unholy power. When over, fear swept through the lands beyond Tausin and a gate was erected.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; A single key was made that would open the gate. It wound through tunnels and mines that exited into the outer empire's deserted landscape. Where the key was stored was never told. To even open it would require a skill that none possessed any longer. The knowledge of such things died out with the steady decrease in dwarf smiths that use to build nearby. Since then, even the dwarves became legends, forgotten by time. Tausin was forgotten; it's dark past never fully discovered.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Thus Exodus's 4th age grew in darkness as Tausin's darkness enslaved all of Scaron save Adrylin. Here, Dragonborn fought hardest of all, keeping back the enemy from the Crystal's temple. As is, each continent has a crystal of balance. The location of the two central Crystals of course are unknown. But they fought to preserve Exodus from the devesation that nature would bring harder on Exodus if even one crystal should shatter.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <br/>
      
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; Ardil's effort to reach Dragonborn with the message was because all other efforts from Dragonborn on Scaron to reach home failed in what could only be described as by the power of darkness not wanting it to be known. Thus until Ardil had given the message to Dragonborn, they knew nothing of what went on on Scaron.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; This new knowledge made Dragonborn step up on their own forces, making ready for the inevitable. They had waited too long. Scaron had been enslaved for centuries now, no word ever escaping as to what had happened.</font>
    </p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0in">
      <font face="Times New Roman, serif" size="2">Now they prepared for the next coming war...</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node LOCALIZED_STYLE_REF="AutomaticLayout.level.root" POSITION="left" ID="ID_842042887" CREATED="1333245321585" MODIFIED="1671241659383" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#ffffff" HGAP_QUANTITY="81 px" VSHIFT_QUANTITY="20 px"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

