<node TEXT="Prime Minister" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_919266032" CREATED="1335897835340" MODIFIED="1335983796565">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_630820485" CREATED="1335897852485" MODIFIED="1335898282127"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>&#xa0;Utis Hieser:</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;In the days of King Fester, Hieser was made prime minister of the High Council of Calmone. Hieser owns a portion of land inside the capital city of Sarsda. This land holds tenants and inns of an upper class.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Friendly to a point but stands by himself in formal banquet settings and parties. He does not trus many people.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance:</b>&#xa0;short crisp greying hair. He wears fancy clothes almost always. roundish face with a small mustach. He is kind of chubby and staunch.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Lord Marshall" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_610288115" CREATED="1335898041245" MODIFIED="1335984310119">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_773937523" CREATED="1335898149985" MODIFIED="1335898264109"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Saul Jennings:</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview:</b>&#xa0;Jennings commands the royal guard consisting of all Black Knights. He holds a mansion inside Sarsda.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Jenson has a mild to flaring temper depending on the day. If his trainees are not fairing well, his temper gets rough. He does not tolerate failure very well.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance:</b>&#xa0;Course semi-long dark brown hair that is usually tied back. His skin is rough, muscular and tanned. There are scars that litter his body and one that runs the length of his face close to his left eye.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Merchants" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1696163719" CREATED="1335898309698" MODIFIED="1335983801557">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1836622594" CREATED="1335898320977" MODIFIED="1335898501518"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Merchants</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      There are numerous merchant guiles inside Sarsda, some even who sit on the High Council. Not born of noble blood, they have earned their place by their own contribution to Calmone by way of their Merchandise that brings wealth to Calmone.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;These Houses are a very powerful influence in the Council because the country itself survives partly off of their sells and foreign exports.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Merchant</b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <i><b>House of Meccles</b></i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;Meccles is a main trader for Calmone in the area of sculptures and art. Those of high classes from other countries highly prize the Meccles art and pay a high price.
    </p>
    <p>
      <i><b>House of Sier-Tav</b></i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;Sier-Tav is the other main trader for Calmone who trades the metals made in the highlands of Sier-Tav. Their craftmanship has been world renowned through the ages. Ambassadors come from across the Drysin Sea just to commission something to be made.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Though Sier-Tav is on the other side of Calmone, they have a guild within Sarsda and a regular transport of goods that ship weekly.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;It has made few friends inside the Council. Sier-Tav is seen as a barbarian province far outside the reaches of Calmone's patrol.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <i>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Marquee of Sier-Tav</i>: Lothin Stingar is lord of the province and a regular attendee and personal friend of King Joshua. Nobody messes with him for two reasons. 1. Personal friend of the King 2. Sier-Tav is known for their extreme hard way of life and constant border protectors.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="High Council" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1484438798" CREATED="1335983920528" MODIFIED="1335984096190">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1153399878" CREATED="1335983938075" MODIFIED="1335983983299"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>High Council</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      Under Utis Hierser as prime minister, the High Council consists of elected deligates (taken from various parts of each province) to represent the major provinces, the treasurer, the Merchant Guiles, and the noble classes.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Bishops of the 9" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1820906692" CREATED="1335984019758" MODIFIED="1370467270532">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_514539098" CREATED="1335984032973" MODIFIED="1335984092966"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Bishops of 9</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      The Bishops consists of the local bishops who have the temples of 9 inside Sarsda. They do not go outside of Sarsda much. Their main purpose is to stay inside their temples and pray and transcribe ancient text.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Priests: </b>The secondary order is to send out Priests to the land to heal the sick and use the magic of the 9 to heal the earth, bless the crops, etc.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;They answer to the High Priest of Calmone alone.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Black Knights" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_799058534" CREATED="1335984123528" MODIFIED="1370467269813">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_735999811" CREATED="1335984133534" MODIFIED="1335984170050"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Black Knights</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;In Sarsda, the Black Knights are the Marshalls of Sarsda and it's surrounding city. Each BK holds his own small portion of land inside the capital, not more than one on the High Council but suitable for his own needs to be called lord.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="B. Southlands - In Order" ID="ID_677779805" CREATED="1335897469660" MODIFIED="1335984344680">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_544097800" CREATED="1335984205045" MODIFIED="1370467272579">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_499526519" CREATED="1335984216159" MODIFIED="1335984266376"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b>Overview: </b>The Southlands surrounds the capital of Sarsda on the Rock Lake. Sarsda does not answer to the count of Southland. It is it's own mini province within the walls of Sarsda.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Southland is primarily a farmland made up of fields and farms dotting the landscape. Grassy hills and valleys make up the majority of Southland.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The rock river borders the west end of Southland and is a major transport route within Calmone.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Count " FOLDED="true" ID="ID_698600255" CREATED="1335984321712" MODIFIED="1335984664156">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1390042700" CREATED="1335984353555" MODIFIED="1335984496880"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Count Malic Jervin:</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview: </b>Jervin is a laid back man who is prone to bringing in festive activities to Southland. He likes entertainment and likes a good competition. With Sarsda so close by, he devised a plan to make his capital city the festive capital.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Jervin has a soft heart for people and the soldiers under his command are well taken care of. The surrounding&#xa0;&#xa0;cities closest to the governing city is well watched over because Jervin cannot stand seeing anyone going without aid.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance: </b>Malic Jervin wears short cropped light brown, at times red hued hair. His face is a bit pudgy but his overall frame is not too overweight. He keeps active outside of his castle going on hunts with his soldiers to keep up the spirits.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Viscounts" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1134475219" CREATED="1335984535139" MODIFIED="1335984666832">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_4273429" CREATED="1335984565276" MODIFIED="1335984649896"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Viscounts</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;Sherrifs underneath Count Jervin who patrols the cities and towns of the province. They have their own manors on site of the cities.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Names of Sherrifs:</b>
    </p>
    <p>
      Markus Lan (town:Hill Valley)
    </p>
    <p>
      Landon Corbin (town: South Hill)
    </p>
    <p>
      Maxus Kain (town: Mayfield)
    </p>
    <p>
      Kisinger Jara (City: Forge City)
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="C. Northlands - In Order" ID="ID_1442582849" CREATED="1335897512622" MODIFIED="1335985200945">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" ID="ID_338333629" CREATED="1335984796943" MODIFIED="1335984804916">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Count" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1044645450" CREATED="1335984808076" MODIFIED="1335984986170">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1916151167" CREATED="1335984822629" MODIFIED="1335984980939"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Count Derril Terrok</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview: </b>Count Derril Terrok holds a large garrison of soldiers. In the common military of Calmone, Trusvill Garrison is the first stop after graduating from trainee.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Count Terrok sends out the fresh soldiers to patrol Northland's vast forests and largely unpopulated terrain to get them experienced in the field.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality: </b>Count Terrok is one of the toughest men in Calmone's military. His character is not for the courts. His temper is for the fields. His sole joy in life is to shout commands. However, he is extremely wise in his tactis so is kept on to train the soldiers.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance: </b>Rough and browned skin. His eyes are like hawks. His hair is almost black with a hint of grey. He has a crooked nose and walks with a cane at times though more for show than anything else.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Dukes" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_513971819" CREATED="1335985010674" MODIFIED="1335985105566">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1962534153" CREATED="1335985017537" MODIFIED="1335985099515"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Lord Kraes Formore</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview: </b>Kraes Foremore is a nobleman related to House Cornith, a very old linage of science learned.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Foremore's father had fallen out of favor with King Fester for unknown reasons and was removed from the capital city to be made a Duke of Northland. This title is not popular among the nobles. There is nothing but forest and bandits in the Northlands. It is more a punishment Palace he was sent to live in.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Kraes Foremore grew up among the forest and made friends with the Border people. His ideals were not those of the capital. He still upheld the land however. If he did not, he would lose the litle bit he had in life.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality: </b>Bitter and vengeful, he has a very secretive nature. He holds to himself and has no serfs. There are only slaves on his land.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance: </b>Foremore has a high brow and receeding hairline that is thin whisps of auburn streaked with grey.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;He has a gated walk and a raspy voice that matches his evil eyes.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Viscounts" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1899507840" CREATED="1335985114861" MODIFIED="1335985251007">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1305213527" CREATED="1335985140656" MODIFIED="1335985177946"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Viscount:</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info: </b>There are no true sherrifs in Northland. The towns that are there are so far apart that they are watched by their own people.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Bishops" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1481837103" CREATED="1335985202633" MODIFIED="1335985252361">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1718392399" CREATED="1335985211544" MODIFIED="1335985248615"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Bishops:</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Priest Damus: </b>Damus acts as the sole Bishop of Northland. The reaches of the White Council has not stretched into the province. He travels a circut route down the unkempt roads.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="D. Vilac - In Order" ID="ID_1749431841" CREATED="1335897538597" MODIFIED="1335897553005">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" ID="ID_1637317606" CREATED="1335985278613" MODIFIED="1335985294143">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
</node>
<node TEXT="Duchess" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1537426218" CREATED="1335985298898" MODIFIED="1335985443352">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1872144651" CREATED="1335985324436" MODIFIED="1335985439842"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Duchess of Vil</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Lady Emlin - Overview:</b>&#xa0;Lady Emlin is King Joshua's only sister and duchess of the royal vacation house of Vil. When finding a day to get away, Joshua takes the family to Vilac to visit his sister in Vil where she has everything ready. Lady Emlin is not simply the duchess of Vil but holds the border of Calmone and Percvam with an ample supply of soldiers at her command.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Ambassadors frequent the Palace Vil before going northward to Sarsda. This way, Lady Emlin can plant spies inside the ambassador suits to know if they hold secrets of harm against the country or King.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Lady Emlin is first and foremost mischievious. She is loving but underneath her skin, she is always searching for trickery.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance:</b>&#xa0;Lady Emlin has long blonde hair that she wears in many different styles. Her body is looked upon by all, men and women as touched by the gods.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Her skin is silk and her eyes sparkle green with laughter.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="E. Cabol - In Order" ID="ID_279591117" CREATED="1335897613906" MODIFIED="1335897632542">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" ID="ID_971037366" CREATED="1335985472062" MODIFIED="1335985477425">
