</node>
<node TEXT="F. Borderlands - In Order" ID="ID_527569918" CREATED="1335897655183" MODIFIED="1336047196037">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_485917959" CREATED="1336047177168" MODIFIED="1336048410564">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1266993821" CREATED="1336048045275" MODIFIED="1336048384887"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Overview</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;The Borderlands are a rough terrain on the eastern edge of Calmone with the Whiteface mountains making up a natural barrier. However, the mountains are home to many wild and dangerous creatures including wild savages relating to the Simrathes, a canibalistic tribe, that live north east of the Drysin Sea.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;It is necessary to keep watch over these mountains. The things that come out of the mountains are not meant to live beside humans. They are more myth than factual to man unless you are unlucky enough to get called to be a Borderwatch at the Tower.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Marquee" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1383762558" CREATED="1336047197743" MODIFIED="1336048412546">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_450019203" CREATED="1336047221346" MODIFIED="1336047873403"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Marquee Victor Kliss</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview:</b>&#xa0;Victor Kliss was appointed marquee of the borderlands in King Fester's reign. He was not a noble but a mercinary who knew his stuff well. At one point he had done a great service for King Fester. In return, King Fester asked Victor to name something he wanted and if it was in his power, Fester would give it to him.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Victor's heart was truly genuine and humble. He knew of the troubles the King had in some of his soldiers. Victor told the King to name him the Marquee of the Borderlands and in return he would turn the King's stubborn highborn trouble makers into true soldiers.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The King agreed quick enough and Victor Kliss was named the Marquee of Borderlands with the Towers as the destination of any soldier who the King decreed trouble for his kingdom.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Borderwatch" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1796021218" CREATED="1336047898852" MODIFIED="1336048413872">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_286334651" CREATED="1336047914982" MODIFIED="1336048041088"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Borderwatch</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;These are common soldiers all the way to high born generals who are expelled from Calmone's military. Under the watch of The Towers, they patrol the Borderlands of Calmone.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
