<node TEXT="1. Bridge of the Heavens" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1849731634" CREATED="1334715926832" MODIFIED="1335486733768">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1998358599" CREATED="1335399918866" MODIFIED="1335399950440"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>The Story</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      The Bridge of Heaven was built when the realm itself was built. It is so wide in length that towns recide on the massive land bridge. Large pillars and tunnels hollow out the underneath to allow the valley below to breath and it's lakes and rivers to flow naturally.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;When first exiting the massive Giant Entrance into Dragonborn's Realm, you are immediately greeted with the pillars of Heaven City.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;This is where any newcomer will be given the tools necessary to get around the rest of the realm. Maps are given out. Words of wisdom and direction of each province and their duke's holdings is clearly shown.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;The rest of the adventure is up to the individual. If you are an ambassador, the King's Royal Knights will escort you to the entrance of the palace (a week's travel away).
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Heaven City is also a Border City with a <b>Marquee</b>. The city is heavily guarded and ready for war being it borders the only entrance into the realm of Dragonborn.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
