<node TEXT="Verlone" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_833952945" CREATED="1334297498112" MODIFIED="1334297505892">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node TEXT="Overview" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1938339345" CREATED="1334705650518" MODIFIED="1370467277110">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_898434984" CREATED="1333248258880" MODIFIED="1334708062591" COLOR="#000000"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>OVERVIEW </u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      Calmone is one of the oldest countries of Elise. It's history dates back farther than man can remember. However in recent centuries, Calmonians have discovered that their own history has vanished. When trying to find records of their ancestory, there is none to be found.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;This has caused a stir of rebelion against the White Council, the most powerful Empire on Exodus whose influence is in every government entity. It is widely known that the White Council plays dirty but to go against them means dire consequences.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;When digging up their past in secret, King Joshua discovers something far greater than his ancestry. It's about an Ancient Race whose tie to Calmone will bring about a revolution in history where Ancients and humans co-exist once again under the banner of Dragonborn.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="People and Religion" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1763050406" CREATED="1334705775542" MODIFIED="1370467274954">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1655828790" CREATED="1333821441556" MODIFIED="1334708070274" COLOR="#000000"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b>PEOPLE AND RELIGION </b>
    </p>
    <p>
      The Religion of Calmone is much like that of all other countries who worship the 9 gods. Each province has a priority to one god over the others depending on what they need most. This is the breakdown of Calmone's provinces:
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>South Valley -</b>&#xa0;Temple to Yilos, Kata, Miea, Fiross, Ousil, Rawtis, and Mayu (South Valley is a major supplier of crops for Calmone so all the gods of farming are prayed to. Major temples are built together in cities as well as in the capitol)
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Sier Tav -</b>&#xa0;Temple to Miea (Seir Tav is a mountain terrain where people must hunt for their food. They sacrifice their hunts to appease Miea and thank the god so the next hunt will be bountiful)
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>North Valley -</b>&#xa0;Temple to Tarris (North Valley is home to Calmone's advanced military training camp so they are always traveling. Tarris is a traveling god and though they risk angering the powerful Yilos who opposes Tarris, Tarris protects the traveler.)
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Reshland -</b>&#xa0;Temple to Mayu (Reshland is a plainland and it's people have no need for most gods. The wind god offers a unique gift of foretelling. Most people living in Reshland are gypsies.)
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
