<node TEXT="Prime Minister" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_432276093" CREATED="1335897835340" MODIFIED="1335983796565">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_960082710" CREATED="1335897852485" MODIFIED="1335898282127"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>&#xa0;Utis Hieser:</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;In the days of King Fester, Hieser was made prime minister of the High Council of Calmone. Hieser owns a portion of land inside the capital city of Sarsda. This land holds tenants and inns of an upper class.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Friendly to a point but stands by himself in formal banquet settings and parties. He does not trus many people.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance:</b>&#xa0;short crisp greying hair. He wears fancy clothes almost always. roundish face with a small mustach. He is kind of chubby and staunch.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Lord Marshall" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_969596912" CREATED="1335898041245" MODIFIED="1335984310119">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1229731494" CREATED="1335898149985" MODIFIED="1335898264109"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Saul Jennings:</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Overview:</b>&#xa0;Jennings commands the royal guard consisting of all Black Knights. He holds a mansion inside Sarsda.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Personality:</b>&#xa0;Jenson has a mild to flaring temper depending on the day. If his trainees are not fairing well, his temper gets rough. He does not tolerate failure very well.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Appearance:</b>&#xa0;Course semi-long dark brown hair that is usually tied back. His skin is rough, muscular and tanned. There are scars that litter his body and one that runs the length of his face close to his left eye.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Merchants" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1313508393" CREATED="1335898309698" MODIFIED="1335983801557">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1801592329" CREATED="1335898320977" MODIFIED="1335898501518"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <u><b>Merchants</b></u>
    </p>
    <p>
      There are numerous merchant guiles inside Sarsda, some even who sit on the High Council. Not born of noble blood, they have earned their place by their own contribution to Calmone by way of their Merchandise that brings wealth to Calmone.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;These Houses are a very powerful influence in the Council because the country itself survives partly off of their sells and foreign exports.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Merchant</b>
    </p>
    <p>
      <i><b>House of Meccles</b></i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;Meccles is a main trader for Calmone in the area of sculptures and art. Those of high classes from other countries highly prize the Meccles art and pay a high price.
    </p>
    <p>
      <i><b>House of Sier-Tav</b></i>
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Info:</b>&#xa0;Sier-Tav is the other main trader for Calmone who trades the metals made in the highlands of Sier-Tav. Their craftmanship has been world renowned through the ages. Ambassadors come from across the Drysin Sea just to commission something to be made.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Though Sier-Tav is on the other side of Calmone, they have a guild within Sarsda and a regular transport of goods that ship weekly.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;It has made few friends inside the Council. Sier-Tav is seen as a barbarian province far outside the reaches of Calmone's patrol.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <i>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Marquee of Sier-Tav</i>: Lothin Stingar is lord of the province and a regular attendee and personal friend of King Joshua. Nobody messes with him for two reasons. 1. Personal friend of the King 2. Sier-Tav is known for their extreme hard way of life and constant border protectors.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="High Council" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_55366350" CREATED="1335983920528" MODIFIED="1335984096190">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1518112495" CREATED="1335983938075" MODIFIED="1335983983299"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>High Council</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      Under Utis Hierser as prime minister, the High Council consists of elected deligates (taken from various parts of each province) to represent the major provinces, the treasurer, the Merchant Guiles, and the noble classes.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Bishops of the 9" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_1798753123" CREATED="1335984019758" MODIFIED="1370467270532">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1629695179" CREATED="1335984032973" MODIFIED="1335984092966"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <b><u>Bishops of 9</u></b>
    </p>
    <p>
      The Bishops consists of the local bishops who have the temples of 9 inside Sarsda. They do not go outside of Sarsda much. Their main purpose is to stay inside their temples and pray and transcribe ancient text.
    </p>
    <p>
      <b>Priests: </b>The secondary order is to send out Priests to the land to heal the sick and use the magic of the 9 to heal the earth, bless the crops, etc.
    </p>
    <p>
      &#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;They answer to the High Priest of Calmone alone.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="Black Knights" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_162537560" CREATED="1335984123528" MODIFIED="1370467269813">
