<node TEXT="3. Social Relationships" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_137572989" CREATED="1378944027555" MODIFIED="1379977363525" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#ccccff">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1545186028" CREATED="1379441094915" MODIFIED="1380593856265" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#dcd0a0"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>ROMANCE</u></b>&#xa0;</font>
    </p>
    <p>
      For the longest time, Tari has found herself in a very cruel and self centered world. How people still got married is beyond her. Most men seem to want to touch her and look at her like an object to be possessed. For years the thought of love was out of the question.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      When Ravage came along it wasn't out of love that she followed him but a need to know herself and her past. As the year progressed she found in Ravage a hurting soul who never took advantage of her but protected her. She began to fall in love with the strange man creature.
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b>Martial Status:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;S </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b>Friends:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Ravage </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b>Allies:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;none </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b>Enemies:</b>&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;Everyone </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3">________________________________ </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>PERSONAL RELATIONSHIPS</u></b>&#xa0;</font>
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>Who is the most important person and why? </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p>
      The only person that matters begins and ends with Ravage. He has shown a kindness to Tari she never knew despite his appearance and rough nature. He also holds the key to finding out where her family came from
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>Who is the person you respect the most? Despise the most? Why? </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p>
      It began with father and mother as they each taught her about life and loved her. When Ravage enters the picture and shows himself as someone who actually does care about things despite his rough exterior, Tari finds a friend in him and someone who could probablly be considered a protector or maybe more.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
<node TEXT="4. History" FOLDED="true" ID="ID_832520608" CREATED="1378944332997" MODIFIED="1379977373927" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#ccccff">
<font NAME="SansSerif" SIZE="12" BOLD="true"/>
<node ID="ID_1567096393" CREATED="1378945178228" MODIFIED="1380594345101" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#dcd0a0"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>Childhood:</u></b>&#xa0;</font>
    </p>
    <p>
      My childhood was filled with playing in the forest and getting into a lot of trouble. I was very rebellious
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>Teenage Years:</u></b>&#xa0; </font>
    </p>
    <p>
      My teen years was hard as I was taken from my carefree world into a school of lessons taught by my father. He told me that I had to be prepared for life as an adult and that started with the sword and how to protect myself. My mother schooled and drilled me in the basics of math and writing, something most people simply did not do. They never told me the reason for the grueling lessons other than that I would need them later in life.
    </p>
    <p>
      <font size="3"><b><u>Adulthood: </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p>
      My adult life is filled with sadness. When I was 21, my family's home was burned to the ground in what can only be described as a magical fire. My parents also died in the fire while I was away selling our goods in the local market. When the city saw what had taken place, itchy fingers pointed at me as if to say I was a danger. Rumors spread until I was run out of town. I left for the larger cities to seek employment. When that didn't work out well, I returned home to where Pug, a tavern owner, took pity and made me a serving girl. This wasn't the life I wanted. I had my fill of men trying to get under my clothes and touching me. In many places this was a common theme among women and they made good money but I felt differently and so was labeled in a bad light.
    </p>
    <p>
      
    </p>
    <p>
      When Ravage came to town and I realized he might have answers, I followed after him.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
<node ID="ID_890613673" CREATED="1378945305588" MODIFIED="1380595217458" BACKGROUND_COLOR="#dcd0a0"><richcontent TYPE="NODE">

<html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>LIFE - IN DETAIL </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>1 How would you describe your life overall</u>? </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      confusing but optomistic
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>2 What is your most memorable moment? </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      father being proud when I beat him at a sword fight. He told me he was extremely proud and celebrated with me by baking a cake though we had little money. My parents seemed to want the best for me despite what we had. I want to prove to them that they were not wasting their time on me. I want to make something of myself
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>3 What has been the most important event in your life</u>? </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      The learning I was given as a teenager. I still remember my parent's faces as they taught me. I have been given the greatest gift anyone can recieve by their parents - love
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>4 What do you consider your greatest achievement? </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      The sword and excellerating at everything my mother taught me. She told me I was exceptional and caught on quickly.
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>5 What is your number one regret? </u></b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      not being there to save my parents lives. It still haunts me.
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>6 When were you the most afraid?</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      when my parents died and the town turned on me. They said I was evil
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>7 What is your greatest fear? Why?</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      not being able to stand strong for my parents. I want to know my past but also am terrified of it at the same time
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>8 What is the most honorable or &#x201c;good&#x201d; thing you&#x2019;ve ever done?</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      In Sauter, I helped save Ravage's life and took him in as a total stranger
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>9 What is the most &#x201c;evil&#x201d; thing you have ever done?</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      thoughts about cutting off pug's balls
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>10 Have you ever been in love?&#xa0;If so, describe what happened.</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      I never wanted to be in love growing up and into adulthood I found men to be pigs for the most part. When Ravage came into my life however, he changed my perception and slowly fell in love with him
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>11 Do you have a notorious or celebrated ancestor/relative?</u></b>&#xa0; </font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3">Gerald Garland and the name of Garland itself</font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <b><u>11a Does this affect you?</u></b>&#xa0;&#xa0;
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      Yes because there is so much mystery surrounding the name. Some say it is notorious for evil and malice. Others say they help behind the scenes staying hidden. I don't know what to believe but I know it's something Ravage holds a bad opinion on. I may not want to know my past if it is steeped in evil.
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      <font size="3"><b><u>12 Do you have any secrets? If so, what are they?</u>&#xa0; </b></font>
    </p>
    <p lang="en">
      I don't have any secrets. Maybe a tiny one and that is to make love with Ravage and be intimate with him. He is hard to get beyond the walls though
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
</richcontent>
</node>
</node>
